<item>
            <title>[FLINK-2912] Potential resource leak due to unclosed RandomAccessFile in StaticFileServerHandler</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2912</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Here is related code in respondAsLeader():&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; RandomAccessFile raf;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
      raf = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RandomAccessFile(file, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;r&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
...
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; fileLength = raf.length();
...
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// write the content.
&lt;/span&gt;    ctx.write(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; DefaultFileRegion(raf.getChannel(), 0, fileLength), ctx.newProgressivePromise());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no close() call to raf before returning.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
